Account Coordinator Job (Telecommunications), Jakarta, Indonesia
Responsibilities
Monroe Consulting Group is recruiting on behalf of one of the largest-independent owners and operators of towers for wireless operators in Indonesia. Its core business is leasing space at its multi-tenant towers for all major wireless operators in Indonesia under long-term lease agreements. Rated as one of Indonesia’s leading companies, our client is seeking a sales professional for the job of Account Manager, to be based in Jakarta, Indonesia. Key job responsibilities and duties will include: Identify potential new business opportunitiesAgenda of the corporate plan with other telecom companies, both in terms of business and technicalNegotiate business and interconnect cooperation with other telecommunications operatorsResolve domestic and international co-operation agreementsResolving problems that occur regarding interconnection and leased lineProvide training to new and existing staff as required Job Requirements  Must be a femaleMinimum GPA is 3.00Strong understanding of customer and market dynamics and requirementsExcellent track record in achieving and exceeding sales targetsStrong analytical skillsHigh-impact leadershipExcellent communication and presentation skillsTeam playerAble to work independentlyFluency in English, both oral and writtenComputer literacy All applications will be treated in the strictest of confidence. If you are a suitable match for this position please send your application to technology@monroeconsulting.com
